node.text: Videos showing people smuggling migrants past Border Patrol checkpoints and flashing thousands of dollars in cash are being posted on TikTok, Texas State Troopers say. This is a new and dangerous tactic to recruit teens to drive migrants from the US-Mexico border to Houston and other Texas cities — with one video offering $4,500 per person they smuggle. CNN's @rosaflorescnn reports.

node.title: Mexican cartels are recruiting teens on TikTok to smuggle migrants

node.text: Do you have questions about Covid-19 vaccine boosters? We spoke to CNN Medical Analyst Dr. Leana Wen to get the answers.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Are boosters unusual when it comes vaccines? Not at all. Many vaccines require multiple doses to achieve the full immune effect. -The polio vaccine requires four doses. -The hepatitis vaccine requires three doses. There are other vaccines that require occasional "boosts" because immunity may wane over time. -The tetanus-diphtheria vaccine is supposed to be given to adults every 10 years. There are other vaccines that need to be administered even more often. -The influenza vaccine needs to be updated every year because there are new strains every season. CNN VACCINE BOOSTERS'.

buttons.text: Visit the COVID-19 Information Center for vaccine resources.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Does a booster mean that the vaccine isn't working? No. We are still learning about Covid-19 and it may be that a third booster shot is needed to finish the series, and after that, we don't need additional immunity It may also be that immunity diminishes over time and an occasional booster will help increase immunity. According to estimates from US Centers for Disease Control and Prevention data, the Covid-19 vaccines protect us from severe illness by about 25 times. Vaccination also reduces the chance of getting Covid-19 by about eight times. CNN VACCINE BOOSTERS'.

node.accessibility_caption: Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Who should be getting boosters at this time? That's something our federal health officials are looking into now. Officials have already said people who are moderately or severely immunocompromised and received the two-dose Pfizer or Moderna vaccines, can receive a third dose now. More guidance is expected soon for other groups. For right now, it's best to speak with your doctor. The decision for a booster dose is probably not a one-size-fits-all recommendation, but an individualized decision depending on your medical circumstances. CNN VACCINE BOOSTERS'.

node.text: On the streets outside the Kabul airport, it's extremely chaotic with Taliban fighters all around and a constant stream of gunfire. "One man shouted at me to cover my face or he wouldn't talk to me. He was carrying a huge makeshift whip," said @clarissawardcnn. "This one fighter just lifted his gun up into the air as if he was about to start firing rounds, so we had to run and take cover."

node.text:
Thousands of residents remain evacuated after the rapidly spreading Caldor Fire charred more than 53,000 acres in Northern California, Cal Fire said Wednesday. In the US, there are 104 large fires burning, mostly in the West, where drought conditions and red flag warnings continue to fuel the raging wildfires, according to the National Interagency Fire Center.⁠
⁠
(📸: Ethan Swope/AP)

Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'What is the timeline? Opening arguments start Wednesday, and the trial is expected to last between six to eight weeks. Prosecutors are expected to make their case that for decades Kelly preyed upon women and girls who dreamed of meeting a superstar, and that his associates were part of a criminal enterprise that lured victims to the singer where some were sexually abused and, at times, filmed being abused. If convicted of the most serious charges, Kelly is facing decades in prison. CNN KELLY'S R.KELLY'STRIAL TRIAL'.

Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Can the public watch the trial? No. The trial will not be televised. The jurors will be the only members of the public with an in-person view of the trial. US District Judge Ann Donnelly ruled not to allow members of the public or media in the courtroom, due in part to Covid-1 restrictions. CNN KELLY'S R.KELLY'STR TRIAL'.

Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'What we may see at R. Kelly's trial? There is a mountain of evidence that is expected to be presented at trial, including videos of alleged abuse and testimony from both victims and former associates of Kelly. Prosecutors hope to convince jurors that Kelly was the leader of a criminal "enterprise" made up of people who served as the singer's managers, bodyguards, drivers, personal assistants, runners and members of his entourage. CNN R. KELLY'S TRIAL'.

Photo by CNN on August 18, 2021. May be an image of text that says 'Prosecutors allege that Kelly had rules that many women and girls he had sex with had to follow: -Some were not permitted to leave their room, go to the bathroom or eat without Kelly's permission. -Some were required to wear baggy clothing when they were not with Kelly, and were not allowed to look at other men -Many were required to call Kelly "Daddy," according to the complaint. CNN KELLY'S R.KELLY'STRIAL TRIAL'.

node.text: Booster doses of the Covid-19 vaccine will be offered to eligible Americans beginning September 20, pending CDC and FDA approval, US health officials said Wednesday. The officials said it's clear that vaccine protection against the coronavirus decreases over time.

node.text:
Former Afghan President Ashraf Ghani, who fled the country Sunday as the Taliban closed in on Kabul, is in the United Arab Emirates, according to the UAE's foreign ministry.⁠
⁠
Tap the link in our bio for the latest on Afghanistan.⁠
⁠
(📸: Alex Brandon/AP)

node.text: Taliban fighters clashed with protesters in Jalalabad, Afghanistan, after they removed the group’s flag from the main square and replaced it with the Afghan flag, three witnesses have told CNN. The protest, which was led by youths, included people of all ages.

node.text:
"I think of Afghanistan each morning, as I slip on a silver bracelet with my dad's name on it and details of where and when he died," said Nick Ochsner, whose father, SFC James Ochsner, was killed in Afghanistan by a roadside bomb in 2005.

"My dad's sacrifice was worth it 16 years ago. I'm not sure I could say the same if he died there today. That makes me sad. And angry. And it should make you sad and angry, too," said Ochsner.

(📸: Ann C. Ochsner)

node.text:
Dozens of artworks once stolen from Jewish collectors by the Nazis in the 1930s and '40s will be exhibited in Manhattan's Jewish Museum starting on Friday. The Nazis are known to have looted hundreds of thousands of pieces, including works by European greats Pablo Picasso, Camille Pissarro and Paul Cézanne. Some were returned to their original owners or their descendants, and many remain missing or are the subject of ongoing legal battles.

(📸: The Jewish Museum)
